g aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tem1665702659575.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tem1665702659575.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tem1665702659575.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tem1665702659575\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Resource Manager (URM)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tem1665702659575__uniface_resource_managerurm__96860\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Uniface Resource Manager (URM) is a command-line utility for manipulating Uniface application resources. It features zip file manipulation functions and support for the standardized archive directory structure and file redirection mechanisms.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tem1665702659575__p_d29729e1_d29730e1_d29731e1\">Although any zip file manipulation tool can be used to package and deploy UAR files, the default Resource Manager has features that are specifically intended for Uniface:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tem1665702659575__li_d15047e1_d15048e1_d15049e1\">Support for Uniface <span class=\"ph filepath\">.uar</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.zip</span> files.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tem1665702659575__li_d15050e1_d15051e1_d15052e1\">Uniface import and data conversion functionality.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tem1665702659575__p_d29732e1_d29733e1_d29734e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpl1665702658861.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpl1665702658861.html\" title=\"Executable for the Uniface Resource Manager, a command line utility for creating and manipulating Uniface archive files and other resources, files and DBMS tables.\">urm</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tem1665702659575__topic_d19822e1_d19823e1_d19824e1_d19825e1_d19826e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d615675e81\">\n            \n Important disclaimer\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tem1665702659575__p_d29738e1_d29739e1_d29740e1\">If not done correctly, deploying a Uniface archive can seriously damage your deployed application. You should make sure your archive contains a consistent set of files and that deploying the archive also results in a consistent application environment.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"tem1665702659575__note_w7672ab1b5b9b5_w7673ab1b5b9_w7674ab1b5_w7675ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> <span class=\"ph\">Rocket®</span> accepts no responsibility for any\n            damages caused by the use of the Resource Manager. Before you deploy any archive, you\n            should stop all Uniface processes (clients, servers, and routers) and you should make an\n            adequate backup of your deployment environment.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cnu1665702658722.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Update a Deployed Application</a><p>To deploy a new version of an application, or just an updated set of objects, you need to copy the new objects (in UARs or folders) to the appropriate locations, and restart the Uniface Router, application servers, and client applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532312\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532312\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Resource Manager (URM) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Resource Manager (URM) The Uniface Resource Manager (URM) is a command-line utility for manipulating Uniface application resources. It features zip file manipulation functions and support for the standardized archive directory structure and file redirection mechanisms. Although any zip file manipulation tool can be used to package and deploy UAR files, the default Resource Manager has features that are specifically intended for Uniface: Support for Uniface .uar and .zip files. Uniface import and data conversion functionality. For more information, see urm . Important disclaimer If not done correctly, deploying a Uniface archive can seriously damage your deployed application. You should make sure your archive contains a consistent set of files and that deploying the archive also results in a consistent application environment. CAUTION: Rocket® accepts no responsibility for any damages caused by the use of the Resource Manager. Before you deploy any archive, you should stop all Uniface processes (clients, servers, and routers) and you should make an adequate backup of your deployment environment. Related Links Update a Deployed Application To deploy a new version of an application, or just an updated set of objects, you need to copy the new objects (in UARs or folders) to the appropriate locations, and restart the Uniface Router, application servers, and client applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}